  "texts": [
    "We then look at coefficient stability across questions.",
    "Figure 3 displays the coefficients of all 24 dummy social predictors in the Social model, for Mixtral, for the 4 questions.",
    "It clearly shows that the association between sociodemographic variables and the distance to the ground truth is not consistent across questions.",
    "For the Mixtral model, the only predictor showing consistent and significantly non-null values is \"Mexico,\" with a positive sign indicating a worse performance for Mexican data compared to US data.",
    "\"Female\" also has positive effects across questions-the language model predicts women's opinions less accurately than men's opinions-but one of them is not significant at the 5 percent level."
  ],
